paragraphs.text: where are these silent faces? they all went away to turn out every light so deep in me me me. hold on, too late!

will i ever see them back again or did they all die by my hand? or were they killed by the old evil ghost who had taken, taken the ocean of all my dreams which were worth to keep deep inside my heart? to get them back from the everflow before they'll fade away. imaginations from the other side! imaginations from the other side! out of the dark, back to the light, then i'll break down the walls around my heart. ...side! where's the ocean's daughter? was peter pan in mordor? no one's there to keep alive, no one's there to keep alive,

do you know? if merlin did exist or frodo wore the ring? did corum kill the gods? or where's the wonderland which young alice had seen? or was it just a dream? i knew the answers, now they're lost for me imaginations from the other side! out of the dark, back to the light, then i'll break down the walls around my heart.

...side! ahahahahahahah! i hope there is a way back with my talisman, so i look into myself, to the days when i was just a child. come follow me to wonderland and see the tale that never ends. don't fear the lion nor the witch. i can't come back, i'm lost, but still i know, there is another world. imaginations from the other side! out of the dark, back to the light, then i'll break down the walls around my heart. ...side!
